commit_message:
Convergence: Do create operation only if action is INIT

All resources that are new will have an INIT state. Instead
of having a complex strategy to decide whether the resource
should be created or updated, just check for the action
to see if it is in the INIT state or not. If it is not, then
always trigger the update workflow.

Also, this fixes a bug where we triggered a create for a
resource without a resource id that originally should've been
updated because it was in UPDATE_FAILED which was the unhandled
case.

Change-Id: I3f2318fecfe76592e8b54e9c09fdf1614197e83f

commit_message:
grub2 bootloader support for uefi boot mode

This implements support for grub2 bootloader for uefi.
The elilo bootloader would be default bootloader. One
can configure to use grub2 by updating ironic.conf as:-
[pxe]
uefi_pxe_config_template=$pybasedir/drivers/modules/pxe_grub_config.template
uefi_pxe_bootfile_name=bootx64.efi

Implements: blueprint uefi-secure-boot-pxe-ilo
Depends-On: I5745fe5c30b0ba1eb67065218dec9c334884007a

Change-Id: Idf7b24cf2f14bef9bebb5efd49a30869c8661572

commit_message:
Add show_resource function to Glance resources (2)

AWS resources will not be changed as they do not support additional
attributes. So 'show' attribute will be presented in their shema, but
will return always None.

This patch adds show_resource method for heat (glance) resources:
 - glance image

For different versions of glance API were implemented different approaches.

commit_message:
Add base resolve method for attributes

Current patch adds two new methods to base class:
 * _resolve_all_attributes - for choosing path for resolving, which
   depends on type of attribute (base or custom).
 * _show_resource - method for resolving base 'show' attribute.
 This method should be re-defined for resources, which use clients with
 specific implementations of 'show' commands.

 New attribute for base class was added - entity, which is used for
 resolving 'show' attribute.

 Tests for Neutron resources and Server resource were updated
 corresponding changes mentioned above.

 Hook for stack_resource class is removed in this patch.

Change-Id: I4ee0a53407739e5590c9a8d12bc7c1e84077f4c4

commit_message:
Change endpoint initialization

Remove endpoint authentication from init of network
context and add it in setup and cleanup. This would
request a token everytime setup() and cleanup() is
called and thus avoid token expiry during long runs.

Change-Id: I971fb9b7eefa6cff30441fd6c9519f8311cddcf9

commit_message:
[image-guide]Fix 'Final config' step the wrong tag in FreeBSD image guide

In FreeBSD image guide, the 'Final config' step use the "title" for it's tag,
actually it is not a title.

This patch fix it, change the tag to "para"

Change-Id: I23c4360be5354e6ffa958a8fde175881c2ab597d
Closes-Bug: #1480505

commit_message:
Less verbose astute.log

Remove shotgun's stdout and stderr
from astute.log. Otherwise, it is barely
possible to page astute.log up and down.
Besides, we have a separate log file
which is /var/log/shotgun.log by default.

Change-Id: I696d81d77db9064fa7fc590d6b5fcfb47c1d7d6f
Closes-Bug: #1480953

commit_message:
Limit alarm actions

Cloud administrator can limit each alarm's maximum actions
for three states, and disables normal user to create
log:// and test:// to avoid bad things happen.

Change-Id: I8a6a49d66c0c51555cec705e4d43c819ede3dc35
Closes-Bug: 1442580

It was possible to lose all edges when if subgraph was created
with skipped tasks.
For example, if we have path a -> b -> c.
And b will be marked as skipped - there is no way to guarantee
that a will be executed earlier than c.

After this patch traversal will be done using all tasks and

Closes-Bug: 1479829
'}]
commit_message:
Preserve original order even if all dependencies are skipped

It was possible to lose all edges when if subgraph was created
with skipped tasks.
For example, if we have path a -> b -> c.
And b will be marked as skipped - there is no way to guarantee
that a will be executed earlier than c.

After this patch traversal will be done using all tasks and
after that filtered tasks will be skipped from sending them
to executor or api.

Change-Id: Iab95774b913c6c4dcd44b5213823e895f1c1f272
Closes-Bug: 1479829

commit_message:
Fix missing pool name in consistency group

This patch makes sure that the entire host is used
in the consistency group host entry.  Previously,
whatever host entry was in the database was being
overwritten by the volume manager's self.host entry,
which doesn't contain a pool.

Change-Id: Ib377429f9cb442b5aaeb2338dd36b6e33f49a41c
Closes-Bug: 1472344

commit_message:
Add missing slash to registry in globals.yml example

Unfortunately we can't account for a missing slash in the task files as
they're not j2 templates. So just update the example comment to try and
help prevent others tripping over this.

commit_message:
Always commit after deployment db operations

This should eliminate a potential race where a depolyment
create doesn't get commited before another engine calls
SoftwareConfigService._refresh_software_deployment

This change also adds a functional test which creates
4 parallel deployments to a server and assert that all 4 end
up in the server metadata.

Change-Id: Iab26aa10bddf3ea569e3ed83a973bcf968964b62
Related-Bug: #1477329

commit_message:
Introduce trove:config to manage custom options

Class trove::config is aim to use trove config resources
to manage custom configurations in trove config files.

This will make end user easy to add their own custom options
in Hiera data.

Change-Id: Ie21abb3f2c0b411948af91916da4112fccc25aa9

commit_message:
Make node-update support more parameters

This patch revises the node-update operation so that node property
changes include 'name', 'role', 'metadata' can be propogated to the
profile layer. This is to support cases where different properties (e.g.
name, role, metadata) may cause profile level update operation.

Change-Id: I35502ec870bf5aa1e835b6182c967ec1ab9a7d18

subject: Specify exception type when adding node from cluster
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-08-04 07:24:10.000000000', 'files': ['senlin/engine/service.py', 'senlin/common/exception.py', 'senlin/api/middleware/fault.py', 'senlin/tests/engine/service/test_clusters.py'], 'message': 'Specify exception type when adding node from cluster

Currently when adding node from cluster, exception is not well handled,
this patch adds NodeNotOrphan type exception for adding one node which
is already owned by other cluster, also raises ProfileTypeNotMatch
exception instead of SenlinBadRequest when profile type is not matched.

Change-Id: I960ec0684da9b1686a7246d8b7ea36a2e18160cf
'}]
commit_message:
Specify exception type when adding node from cluster

Currently when adding node from cluster, exception is not well handled,
this patch adds NodeNotOrphan type exception for adding one node which
is already owned by other cluster, also raises ProfileTypeNotMatch
exception instead of SenlinBadRequest when profile type is not matched.

Change-Id: I960ec0684da9b1686a7246d8b7ea36a2e18160cf

[{'number': 6, 'created': '2015-08-03 19:38:26.000000000', 'files': ['deployment/puppet/rabbitmq/lib/puppet/provider/rabbitmq_user/rabbitmqctl.rb'], 'message': 'Change rabbitmq internal api call to public one

The rabbit_auth_backend_internal:check_user_login is an internal api
call which was removed in Rabbit 3.5.x. Instead we should use
rabbit_access_control:check_user_pass_login which is public and it works
in both 3.3.5 we have now and 3.5.4 we are going to migrate to later.

For further details see
https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-rabbitmq/pull/332

Closes-Bug: #1480991
Change-Id: I6f11e5d4d832c703641b833480092c342c3dc71d'}]
commit_message:
Change rabbitmq internal api call to public one

The rabbit_auth_backend_internal:check_user_login is an internal api
call which was removed in Rabbit 3.5.x. Instead we should use
rabbit_access_control:check_user_pass_login which is public and it works
in both 3.3.5 we have now and 3.5.4 we are going to migrate to later.

For further details see
https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-rabbitmq/pull/332

Closes-Bug: #1480991
Change-Id: I6f11e5d4d832c703641b833480092c342c3dc71d

commit_message:
Controlled shutdown for rescue, shelve, and resize

Rescue, shelve, and resize operations now give the guest OS
a chance to shutdown cleanly before powering off the VM.

The shutdown behavior is defined by the shutdown_timeout
conf parameter

Change-Id: I45699daaf1ed4b5e800f80563cd23f9befd5bb45
Partial-bug: 1204566

The gabbi live tests was ignored during the gate run.

Due to "openstack endpoint list" that returns a empty list:

  https://bugs.launchpad.net/keystone/+bug/1470635

And because the token wasn't passed to gabbit tests.

This change fixes that.

Change-Id: I8e92ac26248b546049a5d7cfea90c861f30e53c8
'}]
commit_message:
gate: fixup gabbi live tests

The gabbi live tests was ignored during the gate run.

Due to "openstack endpoint list" that returns a empty list:

  https://bugs.launchpad.net/keystone/+bug/1470635

And because the token wasn't passed to gabbit tests.

This change fixes that.

It also ensures that the gabbi live test fail
if service url is not present.

Change-Id: I8e92ac26248b546049a5d7cfea90c861f30e53c8

commit_message:
Remove ironic.conf.sample file

Ironic has lot of problems with keeping the ironic.conf.sample file fresh.
We have to generate the conf file every time when we make the changes which
are touched the options. I suggest generate configuration file during
the deployment. Also, Ironic has lot of options are depended from
the local configurations like a host name or a ip address.

Remove ironic.conf.sample and add it to the .gitignore file.
Make the oslo.config.generator.rc more readable.

DocImpact
Generate the sample configuration file during the deployment.

Depends-On: I02f3244ba26cefce973c03addc240df32cd8c48e
Change-Id: I39a30b05a9c0ab3b56d7d45558bd13bbdb61b9b6
CLoses-Bug: 1480831

commit_message:
Make security_groups_client use **kwargs

As we discussed on
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-July/068864.html
All http POST/PUT methods need to contain **kwargs as their arguments.
This patch makes security_groups_client use **kwargs.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: I54792d5f80291b5bdd2f7896e08ac741597c1877
